Time Complexity:

Let n = size of array

    Initial stack fill → O(n)
    Main traversal → O(n)
    Each element pushed & popped at most once

Overall: O(n)


Space Complexity:

    Stack stores elements → O(n)

Overall: O(n)


Approach:

1. Since array is circular:
   - Push all elements into stack initially (simulate wrap-around)

2. Traverse array from right to left:

   - While stack is not empty and top <= current element:
     → pop (not useful as next greater)

3. After popping:
   - If stack is empty → no greater element → set -1
   - Else → top of stack is next greater element

4. Store result in same array (in-place)

5. Push current element back into stack

6. Continue for all elements






class Solution {
    public int[] nextGreaterElements(int[] arr) {
        Stack<Integer> st = new Stack<>();
        for(int i=arr.length-1; i>=0; i--) st.push(arr[i]);
        for(int i=arr.length-1; i>=0; i--){
            while(st.size()>0 && arr[i]>=st.peek()) st.pop();

            int curr = arr[i];

            if(st.size()==0) arr[i]=-1;
            else arr[i]=st.peek();

            st.push(curr);
        }
        return arr;
    }   
}   
